import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['home_score'] = pd.to_numeric(data['home_score'], errors='ignore')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', kde=False)
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='home_team', y='home_score', data=data, estimator=lambda x: sum(x)/len(x))
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which teams have the highest average home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['away_score'] = pd.to_numeric(data['away_score'])
    data['away_team'] = data['away_team'].astype('category')
    avg_away_scores = data.groupby('away_team')['away_score'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='away_team', y='away_score', data=avg_away_scores)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which teams have the highest average away scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
